To install the node.js
Step1: Download the required file from https://nodejs.org/en/
file name:node-v8.11.3-x64.msi
Step2: Provide the separate installation you want to give. 
Path given: S:\Software Execution\nodejs

After the installation is complete. S:\Software Execution\nodejs\ will be automatically added to the System path variable. 

You can check it by running npm command in command prompt. 

While installing node, npm and node both are installed. 
You can check their versions by using following command. 
c:> npm -v  // 5.6.0
c:> node -v // v8.11.3

To install angular run, following command. 
